map

public <T extends java.lang.Enum<T> & AzCategoryId> RequestAttributes<T> map(java.lang.Object javaObject,
                                                                            RequestAttributes<T> azWrapperObject)
                                                                 throws PepException
Description copied from interface: JavaObjectMapper
Performs the mapping of an Object to a RequestAttributes<T> object.

Note: the map method is called with a specific subtype of RequestAttributes<T>. Typically, the map method will test the generic parameter using Attributes.getAzEntity().getAzCategoryId()

Note: the reason for returning a reference to the RequestAttributes is simply to allow for a mapper to reuse some existing state, such as a cached AzEntity, if such a strategy is desired. In such a case, the JavaObjectMapper would need to use the passed in RequestAttributes to obtain the parent PepRequest and then get the AzRequestContext and replace the AzEntity in the AzRequestContext with the cached AzEntity.

Specified by:
map in interface JavaObjectMapper
Returns:
a RequestAttributes object
Throws:
PepException
